node.text:
With the season in sight, we wanted to share a quick refresher on Priority Reservation Days vs. Week-Of Reservation Days

•Priority Reservation Days: On Nov. 6, you will be able to make reservations for the core season (Dec. 8 – April 4) across all of our resorts. As a pass holder, you can lock in up to 7 Priority Reservation Days for the core season in advance, and as many week-of reservations during the season as your pass type and availability allow.

•Week-Of Reservation Days: As our resorts start to open for the season, you can also take advantage of exclusive early season access by making week-of reservations. Booking a week-of reservation does not count against your Priority Reservation Days for the core season.

Take a sneak peek of our new reservation system at the video above.

node.text: Did you know that each night during the winter season, around 35 snowcats hit the mountain to groom over 115 trails into the corduroy you ski or ride every morning? Watch to learn more about what goes into getting the mountain ready for world class skiing. #EpicTogether

node.text: Unlock the secrets of the past and discover our rich mining, skiing and local history on the Silver to Slopes Historic Mining Tour. Tours depart daily at 10am by the Eagle Statue in Mountain Village and at 1pm at the Trail Map near the top of Bonanza Express. #SilverToSlopes

node.title: Silver To Slopes Historic Mountain Tour

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Park City on August 13, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people skiing and nature.

node.text: Explore our mountain's vast 7,300 acres with confidence, learn from world-class instructors, and take your skiing or riding to the next level when you book a lesson with Ski and Ride School. Ski school group and private lessons are now available at the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Park City on August 12, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Have you made it to the Canyons Village Summer Concert Series yet? We're looking forward to tonight's performance by @taylorscottband and are keeping the good times rolling with @turkuazband this Saturday.

And because we can't get enough of the fun, we've extended the Summer Concert Series through Sept 4th with @stillhousejunkies. Join us on the lawn for some tunes and brews!

node.text:
First time skiing or riding? Not sure where to start? Grab an Epic Day Pass for as low as $87 per day this winter, and head to High Meadow Park learning area for an approachable and unforgettable first day on the slopes.

Labor Day is the last chance to lock in the lowest price, start planning your winter adventure now! Check out the link in our bio to learn more about our Epic Day Pass.

node.text: Looking to perfect your putt, or not quite ready for a full 18 on the Canyons Golf Course? Take the whole family out to the Canyons Village Putting Course for a day of fun on the green.

node.text: With over a mile of loops and curves, you can experience the longest mountain coaster in Utah at the Park City Adventure Park. Soar through the trees at speeds up to 25mph and take in the gorgeous mountain scenery as it passes you by.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Park City on August 01, 2021. May be an image of nature, ski slope and snow.

node.text: August is here and that means we're one month closer to the winter season! Today we're reminiscing on powder days from last winter ❄️.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Park City on July 31, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Ever wonder what happens to your chip or candy wrappers once you’re done enjoying them on the mountain? Once you toss the wrapper into one of these designated recycle bins, the magic begins. Our employees sort the wrappers and our partner @pepsico works with @terracycle to turn them into recycled chairs, tables and even terrain park features, coming next season! We are proud to support this initiative as part of our Commitment to Zero waste reduction efforts at Park City Mountain. #SustainabilityStories ♻️

node.text:
Did you know that there are more than 1,000 miles of old silver mines beneath Park City? From the mountains to Main Street, and even far beneath your feet, our unique history as a mining boomtown runs deep—literally—in our town's culture.

Our friends at @skiutah put together an awesome Resort History blog on us, check it out at the link in our bio to learn something you might not have known about Park City Mountain.
